 as a show\u2011off*\n   - *Not open to new ideas*\n   - *Sometimes not good at taking criticism*\n   - *Can be unorganized*\n   None of these points explicitly describe how A behaves in high\u2011stress or emergency situations, so we have **no direct evidence** of his calmness or performance under pressure.\n**Current assessment**\nGiven the available data, Candidate\u202fC still presents the strongest overall profile for a long\u2011distance pilot: explicit reliability, calmness in crisis, rapid correct decision\u2011making, and a generally positive crew atmosphere, despite the noted communication difficulty. The other candidates each lack key evidence in one or more critical areas (calmness, teamwork, leadership, or reliability).\n**Vote:** Candidate\u202fC\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}", "thoughts": "We need to respond as agent_2. We have to follow the format: PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON. We need to consider the discussion so far. Agent 3 just posted a public message summarizing and voting for Candidate C, and asked several questions to agents 2 and 1. As agent 2, we should answer any of those questions we can based on our information. Let's see what info we have.\n\nOur knowledge (from shared mental model) includes:\n\n- Candidate C: difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, not very willing to further his education, keeps calm in a crisis, understands complicated technology, can make correct decisions quickly, (also from agent_3 we have \"excellent attention skills\" but that came from agent_3, not us). We have no explicit examples of communication overcoming difficulty. So we can answer: we have no concrete examples; we only have the statements.\n\n- Candidate B: we have info: very conscientious, handles stress well, good at assessing weather, excellent computer skills, weak memory for numbers, makes nasty remarks about colleagues. No positive teamwork evidence. So we can answer that we have no positive evidence beyond the negative remark.\n\n- Candidate D: we have info: responds to unexpected events adequately, can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously, regarded as a know-it-all, has a hot temper. No explicit leadership examples. So we can answer we have no specific leadership instances.\n\n- Candidate A: we have info: can anticipate dangerous situations, able to see complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities, regarded as a show-off, not open to new ideas, sometimes not good at taking criticism, can be unorganized. No explicit calmness under pressure. So we can answer we have no direct info.\n\nThus we should answer the four questions asked by Agent 3:\n\n1. Candidate C communication examples? Answer: none, only statements.\n\n2. Candidate B teamwork/crew cooperation? Answer: no positive evidence, only negative remark.\n\n3. Candidate D leadership examples? Answer: none.\n\n4. Candidate A calmness under pressure? Answer: none.\n\nWe should also maybe add any additional observations or ask follow-up if needed. But we must answer the questions.\n\nThen we need to give our vote. Based on our assessment, we likely also favor Candidate C, but we need to consider the communication weakness. However we have no new info that would change our view. So we can also vote Candidate C.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE with answers to each question, maybe in bullet form, and then state our vote.\n\nMake sure to only use facts we have. No invented mitigation.\n\nProceed."}
