ples of how Candidate\u202fC manages crew communication despite his reported difficulty? Any incidents where he successfully conveyed critical information?\n2. **Candidate\u202fB \u2013 teamwork / crew\u2011cooperation**\n   *To Agent\u202f1:* Beyond the negative tone issue, have you observed any positive teamwork behaviours from Candidate\u202fB (e.g., supporting colleagues, effective briefings, collaborative problem solving)?\n3. **Candidate\u202fD \u2013 leadership in practice**\n   *To Agent\u202f1:* Are there any specific instances where Candidate\u202fD has taken a leadership role in the cockpit or with ground crew (e.g., leading a de\u2011brief, guiding junior pilots, resolving conflicts)?\n4. **Candidate\u202fA \u2013 calmness under pressure**\n   *To Agent\u202f1:* Have you witnessed Candidate\u202fA in a high\u2011stress or emergency scenario that would demonstrate his calmness and performance under pressure?\n**Preliminary vote**\nGiven the current evidence, Candidate\u202fC still appears to be the strongest overall fit for a long\u2011distance pilot, but the lack of concrete communication evidence keeps my confidence moderate. I will maintain my vote for **Candidate\u202fC** while awaiting the additional information requested above.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}", "thoughts": "We need to respond as agent_3 now. The previous turn was from agent_2 answering the questions. Now as agent_3, we should consider the new info. Agent_2 just confirmed no concrete examples for C communication, no positive teamwork for B, no leadership for D, no calmness for A. So we have all gaps. We need to possibly ask further questions to fill gaps, maybe ask other agents (agent_1) for any info we lack. We have no info on candidate B's teamwork positive aspects, candidate D's leadership examples, candidate A's calmness, candidate C's communication examples. Agent_2 says none. Maybe agent_1 might have some info? We haven't asked agent_1 about